.Dd January 23, 2012
.Dt USBIFF 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm usbiff
.Nd general-purpose notification daemon
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl c Ar config
.Op Fl fv
.Op Ar
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility displays notifications using a USB Webmail (sic) Notifier device when new mail arrive in
.Ar filename
or when the process is siganled using
.Dv SIGUSR1
or
.Dv SIGUSR2 .
.Pp
If no
.Ar file
is provided and no configuration file is found,
.Nm
will look for the user's mailbox on the system: if a
.Ev MAIL
environment variable is defined, the pathname will be used as the user's mailbox location, otherwise the pathname is constructed as
.Ar /var/mail/
followed by the value of the
.Ev USER
environment variable.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width ".Fl -c Ar config"
.It Fl c Ar config
Read configuration from the
.Ar config
file.
.It Fl f
Run in the foreground.  By default,
.Nm
forks and detach from the controlling terminal.
.It Fl v
Increase verbosity. Implies
.Fl f .
.El
.\" The following commands should be uncommented and
.\" used where appropriate.
.\" .Sh IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
.\" This next command is for sections 1, 6, 7 and 8 only.
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width ".Ev MAIL"
.It Ev MAIL
Location of the user's mailbox.
.It Ev USER
Login name of the user executing
.Nm .
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "~/.usbiffrc"
.It ~/.usbiffrc
Default location of
.Nm
configuration file.
.El
